// SPERT AHP — Firestore rules pointer (v0.12.2)
//
// This file is intentionally NOT the source of truth.
//
// The canonical, suite-wide Firestore ruleset lives in the SPERT landing-
// page repo at:
//
//   spert-landing-page/firestore.rules
//
// The live deployed rules are whatever currently sits in the Firebase
// Console for project `spert-suite`. When making a rules change, the
// workflow is:
//
//   1. Open the Firebase Console rules editor for `spert-suite`.
//   2. Start FROM the live console rules (not from any checked-in file).
//   3. Edit, validate in the console simulator, and publish.
//   4. Mirror the published version back into
//      spert-landing-page/firestore.rules and commit there.
//
// Why this file exists at all: Firebase tooling and a few editors look
// for `firestore.rules` at repo root. Keeping a stub here prevents
// accidental project-level deploys (`firebase deploy --only
// firestore:rules`) from silently uploading nothing while still making
// it obvious to a reader that the AHP repo is not where rules are
// authored.
//
// Do not paste-replace the live rules from this file. It is a pointer.
//
// History: prior to v0.12.2 this file held a stale partial copy of the
// AHP-specific rules and was missing the entire suite-wide invitation
// infrastructure (spertsuite_invitations, spertsuite_profiles,
// spertsuite_rate_limits, spertsuite_notification_throttle). Replaced
// with this pointer to eliminate divergence risk — see the v0.12.2
// security audit, finding F1.
